    "notes": [
      "Three-player JS/Python control for same-frame point materialization.",
      "p0 and p1 share the same start and endpoint, but p1 starts with printing false, so no point body is inserted before p0's collision check.",
      "The live p1 head is not inserted into the world by itself, so p0 survives and the world body count remains zero.",
      "Forced trail state keeps setup direct and avoids setup-time printManager.start() or stop() side effects."
    ]
  },
